welcome_message_body: Welcome to Bagong Silangan, a charming city known for its vibrant culture, beautiful landscapes, and friendly locals. We invite you to explore our city and enjoy all it has to offer.

terminals.name: Terminal 1
terminals.description: The oldest and largest terminal at Ninoy Aquino International Airport, serving both international and domestic flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 2
terminals.description: Also known as the Centennial Terminal, it primarily serves international flights for Philippine Airlines.

terminals.name: Terminal 3
terminals.description: The newest and largest terminal at Ninoy Aquino International Airport, serving both international and domestic flights.

terminals.name: Terminal 4
terminals.description: Also known as the Domestic Terminal, it mainly serves domestic flights for low-cost carriers.

wifi.note: Limited to 2 hours per device per day.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Baler Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Cargo Terminal
terminals.description: The cargo terminal at Baler Airport handles all freight and cargo operations.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.
